This paper deals with the representation of evidential confirmation in AI, which is a subfield of computer science. The paper discusses the use of probability theory and its limitations, which suggests that it belongs to the sub-category of cs.AI. The paper also discusses the transformation of probability, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (machine learning). The use of axiomatic basis and conditional independence suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.IT (information theory). The paper also discusses the representation of uncertain reasoning, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of cs.SI (social and information networks) and cs.CC (computational complexity).
